    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, preserved in a state that defies its age. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW rotary power plant, featuring a flawlessly functioning sequential twin-turbocharger setup that provides a seamless boost transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, benefiting from the factory double-wishbone suspension and lightweight aluminum components that maintain the legendary 50/50 weight distribution. All vacuum lines have been meticulously inspected, and the cooling system remains optimized for thermal efficiency without compromising the OEM aesthetic. The 5-speed manual transmission offers crisp, tactile engagement through every gate, paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential that ensures optimal torque vectoring. This is a collector-tier example with zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a factory-fresh interior, representing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
